Subject: Oracle collection errors
Description: Trying to target 2 oracle hosts (ETS-VAPRD-ODA0.CDC.NICUSA.COM, ETS-VADEV-ODA0.CDC.NICUSA.COM) for DB scans (1-Oracle_PermissionsScan). The connection shows access granted but the job shows error. Upon inspection we see a bunch of messages referring to SQL key constraints. Sample: Violation of UNIQUE KEY constraint 'SA_Oracle_Parameters_Id'. Cannot insert duplicate key in object 'dbo.SA_Oracle_Parameters'. The duplicate key value is Failed to collect permissions: System.Data.SqlClient.SqlException (0x80131904): Violation of UNIQUE KEY constraint 'SA_Oracle_Parameters_Id'. Cannot insert duplicate key in object 'dbo.SA_Oracle_Parameters'. The duplicate key value is (tablespace_encryption, 9, 9).
Solution_Comment__c: We discovered that there were duplicate entries under the sa_database_id column which was creating the error presented in this ticket. We removed the duplicate entries and reran the Oracle permissions scan.
